Rating: 4
My family and I really enjoyed this delicious, not-overly-sweet frosting on a spice cake. I made the recipe exactly as written using mostly organic ingredients and plenty of orange zest. In my opinion, the secret in getting a great texture for proper frosting here is in using cultured, unsalted butter that is much lower in water content than the typical store brands. This has become my standard cream cheese frosting recipe.

