Rating: 3
Yummy. I loved this recipe. I tweaked it a bit; I added another stick of butter (to lighten the texture), a Tablespoon of Cointreau (for more orangey zing) and substituted the sour cream with heavy cream (for a smoother flavor). This might appeal to those of you who like buttercreams a bit more than traditional cream cheese frosting. To me this recipe is a little too 'cheesy' and dense as is. Good for a carrot cake but a bit much for a spice cake. Enjoy!

